# Styling & UI Patterns

## UI Component Library
- **Base**: shadcn/ui components in [src/components/ui/](mdc:src/components/ui/)
- **Config**: [components.json](mdc:components.json) - shadcn/ui configuration
- **Icons**: Lucide React (configured as default icon library)
- **Primitives**: Radix UI components for accessibility

## Tailwind CSS Setup
- **Version**: Tailwind CSS 4.1.13
- **Base Styles**: [src/styles/globals.css](mdc:src/styles/globals.css)
- **CSS Variables**: Enabled for theme customization
- **Animations**: `tailwindcss-animate` plugin for transitions

## Styling Conventions
```tsx
// Use cn() utility for conditional classes
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

<div className={cn(
  'base-classes',
  {
    'conditional-class': condition,
    'another-class': anotherCondition
  }
)} />

// Standard Tailwind patterns
<div className="flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 rounded-lg" />
```

## CSS File Organization
- **Global Styles**: [src/styles/globals.css](mdc:src/styles/globals.css)
- **Layout Styles**: [src/styles/layout.css](mdc:src/styles/layout.css)
- **Feature Styles**: Page-specific CSS (e.g., `home-page.css`, `dashboard.css`)
- **Component Styles**: Import specific CSS files when needed

## Component Styling Patterns
- **Layout Components**: Grid and flexbox for responsive layouts
- **Cards**: Use shadcn/ui Card components for content containers
- **Forms**: shadcn/ui Input, Label, Button components
- **Navigation**: Custom styling with active state management

## Responsive Design
```tsx
// Mobile-first responsive classes
<div className="grid md:grid-cols-[220px_1fr] lg:grid-cols-[280px_1fr]" />

// Responsive spacing and sizing
<div className="p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8" />
```

## Color System
- **CSS Variables**: Use Tailwind's CSS variable system
- **Theme Colors**: Defined in global CSS with proper contrast ratios
- **Semantic Colors**: Background, foreground, muted, accent variations

## Animation & Effects
- **Transitions**: Use `tailwindcss-animate` classes
- **Hover States**: Interactive elements should have hover effects
- **Focus States**: Accessible focus indicators for keyboard navigation

## Gradient Components
- **Custom Gradients**: Dedicated components in [src/components/gradients/](mdc:src/components/gradients/)
- **Background Effects**: SVG-based background patterns and effects
- **Examples**: `DashboardGradient`, `HomePageBackground`

## Image Handling
- **Next.js Image**: Use `next/image` for optimized images
- **SVG Icons**: Stored in `/public/assets/icons/`
- **Background Images**: SVG patterns in `/public/assets/background/`

## Accessibility Standards
- **Semantic HTML**: Use proper HTML elements
- **ARIA Labels**: For complex interactive elements
- **Keyboard Navigation**: Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- **Color Contrast**: Follow WCAG guidelines for text contrast